    <item>
      <title>Truly Breakable Weapons - a durability overhaul</title>
      <author>cargocult</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/685991</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/685991#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">44a93311781ac307da3f337b7a36107cd0387527</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 30 Jun 2026 14:11:50 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a2edac3586f0.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a2edac3a4411.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a2edad6695ef.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a2edad681f41.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a2edad62b545.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a2edad5b2508.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a2edad649f0c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a2edad602694.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a2edad65be83.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a2edad635418.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Hitbox lengths fixed&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Re-fused weapons now have their intact hitbox lengths. The tradeoff is that bare hilts also have the same hitbox length, but since they do 1 damage and break in 1 hit, you're unlikely to actually use it, right? A week of research could not figure out how to make the fuse material add to the hitbox, even though vanilla attachments seem to do this, replicating their methods did not work.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;AI usage disclaimer required by site rules&lt;/h1&gt;This mod was in my head for a long time and only became something I was willing to take on thanks to the level of automation possible with AI for a non-programmer:&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;to write the Python scripts that batch process the 73 base weapon actors into 146 new actors&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;to write the Python scripts that assemble test builds of the mod for researching complex subjects such as mapping of the fuse naming system, probing the workings of the attachment scaling system, processing models into collision polytopes, and so on&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Fun facts:&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Development started May 23rd&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;283 test builds of the mod so far, mostly for research&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Using ChatGPT 5.5 via Codex&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Developed skills (reusable shareable tools) for AIs to work on most of TOTK's files and systems (these will be available open source)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Gameplay summary&lt;/h1&gt;&#13;
    When your weapons break, it's no longer the end!&lt;ul&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;They now shatter into a broken hilt and a blade, which can be re-fused back together. That means you can keep using your favorite weapon a bit longer, but not forever.&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;When the weapon breaks, you have to grab the hilt, and then scramble after the blade, all in the midst of combat.&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;The blades can't be picked up, so fuse it or lose it.&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;The hilt is near useless except as a handle.&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Re-fused weapons have the same power as the original weapon.&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;...but you used up the fuse slot to reattach the blade. That means an unbroken one is always better.&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;You can mix and match blades across families to create realistic-looking new and interesting weapon combinations, with new names.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Design concept&lt;/h1&gt;My goal is usually showing "what if game design choices had been slightly different? Can it be more fun?". This forms part of the &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/collections/209319"&gt;Cargocult Cinematic Universe&lt;/a&gt;- uh, I mean, modular gameplay reworks.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I am pretty pleased with this one.&#13;
&#13;
I think this design works because you still have to think about durability, but you don't get your toys just taken away when you play with them too much. In fact the scramble to catch the hilt and re-fuse is a fun added mini-mini-game. So is the naming, like if you accidentally fuse some junk to the hilt instead of the blade.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; I am working on an extension adding local blacksmiths, who can restore re-fused weapons back into one piece, which will make it feel even more like you're not punished for playing with them (but they're not just unbreakable - you still have to do a little work of catching and re-fusing then bringing them back to town, and replacing any special fuse materials)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Weapon Scope&lt;/h1&gt;&#13;
    v1 covers &lt;strong&gt;73 swords, two-handed swords and spears&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#13;
    The aim was to cover all of the logical choices - real weapons which make sense to be included, that have blades that break and would want to be reattached. I didn't include sticks, clubs and so on.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#13;
    Weapon families covered:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#13;
    &lt;ul&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Rusty&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Traveler’s&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Soldier’s&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Knight’s&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Royal&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Royal Guard’s&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Feathered / Rito&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Forest Dweller’s&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Gerudo&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Goron&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Zora&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Champion weapons&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Yiga / Sheikah&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Gloom&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Amiibo&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
    &lt;/ul&gt;&#13;
&#13;
    &lt;h2&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Compatibility Notes&lt;/h1&gt;&#13;
    &lt;b&gt;Install with TKMM!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod touches many TOTK files and systems with a lot of new content. Manual installs are going to have problems.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Although it edits lots of base weapons, the edit is actually small (just adding the breakability). It should be compatible with lots of other mods, but I can't guarantee it.&lt;h2&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Known Problems&lt;/h1&gt;&#13;
    Due to the huge number of possible combinations it's not been possible to test everything. If you see anything wrong, please let me know so I can track it down and fix it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#13;
    &lt;ul&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;All hilts are supposed to be 1-damage 1-durability; with the blade getting the rest of the source weapon's damage and durability. TOTK's evil UI decision to lie about spear and largesword damage meant I had to fudge them a bit, so they are not 1.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fused sizes of blades are sometimes not exactly accurate. The system for scaling is really weird and complicated and the current design is a best middle ground. If you find any stupid examples, please tell me.&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
      &lt;li&gt;Broken hilts still have the swipe graphical effect of their longer parent, especially obvious on two-handed swords. I couldn't figure out how to make this align without opening a whole new can of worms.&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
    &lt;/ul&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/truly_breakable_weapons_v10.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/truly_breakable_weapons_v11.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/truly_breakable_weapons_v12.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Gameplay</category>
      <category>Gameplay</category>
    </item>
