    <item>
      <title>Fully Buffed Armor</title>
      <author>DepthDweller</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/686275</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/686275#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">54eb08671387bc1ab74076f06d9d7a76b25bf718</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 18:34:41 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a30415e272c4.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a304177a4de3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a30417c1011a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Caelum Sovereign Set (Fully Buffed Armor)&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Author:&lt;/strong&gt; DepthDweller&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Version:&lt;/strong&gt; 1.0.0&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Game Version:&lt;/strong&gt; 1.2.1&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1&gt;⚠️ Upgrade Warning&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do NOT upgrade the Caelum Sovereign Set.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Upgrading any piece of the armor will break its custom defense values and revert that piece back to the default Ember Set defense progression.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To maintain the intended &lt;strong&gt;84 defense per piece (252 total defense)&lt;/strong&gt;, keep all three armor pieces &lt;u&gt;unupgraded.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h1&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Caelum Sovereign Set&lt;/strong&gt; is a vibrant, fully buffed armor set available from three special chests placed in the Room of Awakening on the Great Sky Island.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Included Armor Pieces&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Caelum Crown&lt;/strong&gt; (Head)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Caelum Vestment&lt;/strong&gt; (Chest) — Pink&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Caelum Greaves&lt;/strong&gt; (Legs) — Purple&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Each armor piece provides:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;84 Defense per piece&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;252 Total Defense&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maximum defense at every upgrade level&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Native &lt;strong&gt;Hot Weather Attack (Attack Up)&lt;/strong&gt; effect&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;The result is a powerful endgame-quality armor set that can be obtained immediately upon reaching the chests.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2&gt;How to Obtain&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3&gt;You do NOT need to start a new game.&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Simply install the mod and travel to the &lt;strong&gt;Room of Awakening&lt;/strong&gt; on the Great Sky Island.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Three Zonai chests await at the altar near where Link first wakes up. Open them to receive the complete Caelum Sovereign Set.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For new saves, the armor can be collected within moments of beginning the game.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Important Notes&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Known Issue&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h1&gt;In the inventory, the &lt;strong&gt;Caelum Crown&lt;/strong&gt; currently appears red. When equipped, however, it displays the default, base game color.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I am currently working on a fix for this issue.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Ember Set Information&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h1&gt;This mod is built using the Ember Set as its foundation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;While this mod is installed, obtaining Ember armor from its normal in-game locations will award the corresponding Caelum Sovereign armor piece instead.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Players who already possessed Ember armor before installing the mod may have both Ember and Caelum armor in their inventory.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Compatibility&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Legend of Zelda: Tears of the Kingdom&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Version &lt;strong&gt;1.2.1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Works on any supported emulator&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;TKMM is &lt;strong&gt;not required&lt;/strong&gt;, but is &lt;strong&gt;highly recommended&lt;/strong&gt; for users who manage multiple mods.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/fullybuffedarmor_100_game_ver_121_.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Armor set</category>
      <category>Models</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Kingdom Hearts Keyblades</title>
      <author>Samus_Aran</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/686224</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/686224#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">f3f658e01548ec1a996e08a3bec64c0d3778b8de</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 14:54:35 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a3010d05e2b8.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a300fdbaf86c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a300fd8e05a7.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6a3010c94ed23.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod replaces most one-handed swords with various Keyblades from throughout the Kingdom Hearts series. Each Keyblade has a custom inventory name and description.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Check out &lt;a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vR-Ye0ax2aI_fe8fUzsxTtOkHHWym8fdA6y5RqvnnBSRHwNurGwHrS5BfOchtVSbZf4qdO5kr4H_NfF/pubhtml"&gt;this list&lt;/a&gt; to see which swords were replaced by which Keyblade.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For the best immersion, I'd also recommend these mods:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#13;
&lt;ul class="[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3"&gt;&#13;
